Message.MsgText: ERROR_REQUIRED_ATTRIBUTE_WHEN_SET=CWWCW5006E: A required attribute of {0} is missing. The attribute {1} is required when attribute {2} is set to {3}.
Message.Explanation: You must supply a value for the specified attribute.
Message.UserResponse: Use either the administrative console or the command line scripting tool to add the required attribute.

Message.MsgText: ERROR_ATTRIBUTE_VALUE_OUT_OF_RANGE=CWWCW5031E: An attribute of {0} is out of range. {1} needs a value between {2} and {3}.
Message.Explanation: The value given for the specified attribute is not within the permitted range of values.
Message.UserResponse: Use either the administrative console or the command line scripting tool to set a valid value for the attribute.

Message.MsgText: ERROR_AUTH_DATA_ALIAS_NOT_LOCATED=CWWCW5050E: The alias {0} to the JAASAuthData entry, specified for {1} {2}, matches no configured JAASAuthData entries in security.xml.
Message.Explanation: The specified authentication alias has not been recognised.
Message.UserResponse: Use either the administrative console or the command line scripting tool to configure the appropriate authentication alias entry.

Message.MsgText: ERROR_REQUIRED_ATTRIBUTE=CWWCW5003E: A required attribute of {0} is missing. The attribute {1} must have a value.
Message.Explanation: You must supply a value for the specified attribute.
Message.UserResponse: Use either the administrative console or the command line scripting tool to add the required attribute.

Message.MsgText: ERROR_INVALID_ATTRIBUTE_VALUE=CWWCW5030E: An attribute of {0} has an invalid value. {1} should be {2}
Message.Explanation: The value given for the specified attribute is not valid.
Message.UserResponse: Use either the administrative console or the command line scripting tool to set a valid value for the attribute.

Message.MsgText: ERROR_DUPLICATE_NAME=CWWCW5008E: The name attribute of {0} must be unique. The name {1} is already in use.
Message.Explanation: The name that you specified for the new object is already in use.
Message.UserResponse: Use either the administrative console or the command line scripting tool to create the object using a different name.

Message.MsgText: ERROR_NULL_VALIDATION_OBJECT=CWWCW5100E: The object passed in for validation was null or not valid.
Message.Explanation: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .
Ensure that the name has been entered correctly, or use either the administrative console or the command line scripting tool to add the required object.

Message.MsgText: ERROR_REQUIRED_ATTRIBUTE_EITHER=CWWCW5007E: A required attribute of {0} is missing. Either {1} or {2} is required.
Message.Explanation: One of the attributes is mandatory.
Message.UserResponse: Use either the administrative console or the command line scripting tool to add one of the required attributes.

Message.MsgText: ERROR_REQUIRED_CONFIG_FILE=CWWCW5061E: A required file is missing. The file {0} must exist.
Message.Explanation: A configuration object has referred to an object: the object and its file do not exist. The first time you create the object, the file will be created.
Message.UserResponse: Use either the administrative console or the command line scripting tool to create the required object and file, or check that the reference is correct.
